                            <comment id="17217459" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2020 09:29:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The delay is a bit special as it has its own block, so you need to have an extra end to end the delay, so the mock:result can be on the outer side.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; .delay(1000).asyncDelayed().end()&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
